Each object that can have an index should have just one text box which can be used to specify the indices as follows:

[<index math>][<index math>] etc.

A split on "[" can be used to extract the <index math> fields remembering to remove the closing bracket.  You can then loop through this and add them with arrayDimension 0, 1, 2, etc.  

The number of <index math> fields should be equal to the number of dimensions for the object being indexed.  If this is not true, then an error should be generated.


